"{\"uid\": \"flotrack.org-articles-12758251-aau-junior-olympics-track-and-field-2024-results-on-day-7\", \"text\": \"Adidas Indoor Nationals  Redlands Invitational  Texas Distance Festival  Chandler Rotary Invite  W&L Outdoor T&F Carnival  Run Rome the Marathon  David Noble Relays  Emory Thrills in the Hills  WashU Distance Carnival  Jim Taylor Duals  Doc Jopson Invitational  2026 FSU Relays  Continental Tour: Maurie Plant Meet  WashU Invite  Monmouth Home Opener  After Day 7 of the AAU Junior Olympics concludes, only one day of events remains.  9-year-old Cerenity Bell from Raleigh, NC set a new national record in the girls 200m final, going 27.18.  Friday features finals in the 4x800m relay for ages 11 through 18, as well as the 200m for all ages.  The 2024 Junior Olympics Track and Field competition isstreaming live on FloTrack, MileSplit and the FloSports app.Highlights, replays and breaking news are on both platforms.  Do not miss all the track and field season action streaming on FloTrack.Check out the FloTrack schedule for more events.  Video footage from each event will be archived and stored in a video library for FloTrack subscribers to watch for the duration of their subscriptions.  Tags:  Get the most important Track & Field stories delivered straight to your inbox.  \\u00a92006 - Present FloSports, Inc. All rights reserved.\"}"